{"id":"widows","term":"Widows","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>To be treated with kindness (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Exodus 22:22\">Ex. 22:22</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Deuteronomy 14:29\">Deut. 14:29</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Deuteronomy 16:11\">16:11</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Deuteronomy 16:14\">14</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Deuteronomy 24:17\">24:17</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Deuteronomy 24:19\">19-21</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Deuteronomy 26:12\">26:12</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Deuteronomy 27:19\">27:19</a>, etc.). In the New Testament the same tender regard for them is inculcated (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Acts 6:1\">Acts 6:1-6</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Timothy 5:3\">1 Tim. 5:3-16</a>) and exhibited.</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Exodus 22:22","Deuteronomy 14:29","Deuteronomy 16:11","Deuteronomy 16:14","Deuteronomy 24:17","Deuteronomy 24:19","Deuteronomy 26:12","Deuteronomy 27:19","Acts 6:1","1 Timothy 5:3"]}